  "text": "Intraperitoneal glucose and insulin tolerance tests. Separate cohorts of 8 -10 13-wk-old transgenic (Tg) and control littermates were injected intraperitoneally with glucose (1 g/kg). Animals were fasted for 6 h prior to the glucose tolerance test [CITATION_1] . For the insulin tolerance test, food was removed 2 h prior to insulin injection. Serum samples were collected at the indicated time points shown in the RESULTS.",
